{"meta":{"authors":[{"fullname":"José I. Cabezón","id":"7"}],"title":"Empowerment","dates":{"created_at":"2013-09-15 04:08:18 UTC","updated_at":"2014-02-05 16:15:38 UTC"}},"nodes":[{"index":0,"parent_index":-1,"title":"Empowerment"},{"title":"Description","index":1,"parent_index":0,"body":" <p>Empowerments are the doorway (sgo) into tantric yogic practice, and are designed to ritually transform a yogi's body and mind in ways that allow for that practice to be successful. Empowerments also serve as social gateways, or ritual ceremonies that allow full participation in a tantric community<\/p> <p>This category also includes empowerments that function more simply as public rituals and blessings, independent of any soteriological goals.<\/p> "},{"title":"Related Terms","index":2,"parent_index":0,"body":" <p>dbang chog, bka' dbang, dbang bskur ba'i cho ga, smin byed<\/p> "},{"title":"Example Texts","index":3,"parent_index":0,"body":" <ul> <li><a href=\"http:\/\/tbrc.org\/#!rid=W10595\">bde mchog snyan brgyud lus dkyil gyi dbang chog<\/a> <\/li> <li>See also <a href=\"http:\/\/tbrc.org\/#!rid=T48\">dbang chog<\/a><\/li> <\/ul> "},{"title":"Secondary Sources","index":4,"parent_index":0,"body":" <p><!--[if gte mso 9]><xml> Normal 0 false false false MicrosoftInternetExplorer4 <\/xml><![endif]--><!--[if gte mso 9]><xml> <\/xml><![endif]--><!-- --><!--[if gte mso 10]> <mce:style><! \/* Style Definitions *\/ table.MsoNormalTable {mso-style-name:\"Table Normal\"; mso-tstyle-rowband-size:0; mso-tstyle-colband-size:0; mso-style-noshow:yes; mso-style-parent:\"\"; mso-padding-alt:0in 5.4pt 0in 5.4pt; mso-para-margin:0in; mso-para-margin-bottom:.0001pt; mso-pagination:widow-orphan; font-size:10.0pt; font-family:\"Times New Roman\"; mso-ansi-language:#0400; mso-fareast-language:#0400; mso-bidi-language<![endif]--> <!--[endif]--><\/p> <p><!--[if gte mso 9]><xml> <w:WordDocument> <w:View>Normal<\/w:View> <w:Zoom>0<\/w:Zoom> <w:PunctuationKerning \/> <w:ValidateAgainstSchemas \/> <w:Sav